    "updated_at": "2016-12-02T13:48:49Z",
    "body": "@VinciShark i don't exactly understand your use case, but you don't need the HWDN of the offscreen browser window, the [`'paint'`](http://electron.atom.io/docs/api/web-contents/#event-paint) event has the `image` parameter that is a `NativeImage` which has a [`getBitmap`](http://electron.atom.io/docs/api/native-image/#imagegetbitmap) method to get the bitmap representation of the browser window as a Buffer."
